org.apache.juneau

Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.juneau.Session
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParserSession, SerializerSession, VarResolverSession

    public abstract class Session
extends Object
    A one-time-use non-thread-safe object that's meant to be used once and then thrown away.

    Serializers and parsers use context objects to retrieve config properties and to use it as a scratchpad during serialize and parse actions.

    Author:
    James Bognar (james.bognar@salesforce.com)
    See Also:
    ContextFactory
